bypasses structured logging, can leak potentially sensitive prompt/response content to stderr in production, and is unrelated to the stated fix. Mixing debugging aids into an unrelated feature branch makes review harder and risks accidental shipment."},{"body":"Remove the unconditional `--debug-file` argument addition in `src/adapters/process_backend.rs` (lines ~429-445 in the diff) that writes a debug log for every Claude invocation to `runtime/temp/{invocation_id}.claude-debug.log`. This is unrelated to the artifact-metadata fix and would generate debug files for every invocation in production.","rationale":"Unconditionally creating debug log files for every invocation is a disk-space and information-disclosure concern. If debug logging is needed, it should be opt-in (e.g., behind a CLI flag or config setting). This change is also outside the scope of the artifact-metadata fix."},{"body":"Exclude the `result` symlink change from the branch. The diff shows the Nix store path in the `result` symlink changing — this is a local build artifact that should not be version-controlled.","rationale":"The `result` symlink points to a Nix store path that is machine-specific. Committing it creates noise in diffs and can cause confusion for other developers with different Nix store paths."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"d8f5aa96-0d5a-4173-8020-cf7a557d467e"}
